It is the action, and not the fortune, or ſituation in life, by which the ſenſible and diſcerning characteriſe mankind. It is not the beautiful face,—the graceful form,—the lovely look;—It is not theſe that conſtitute beauty, when the mind is deformed;


Honor and Fame from no condition riſe:

Act well your part, there all the honor lies.
